    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="935"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d935">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00115A Pacific War/730: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-03">October 3,
                            1943</date>.<lb/>[Received October 3—9:26 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6170. American interests, occupied China. Legation’s 5692, September 13. American
                    internees boarding <hi rend="italic">Teia Maru</hi>
                    <note n="47" xml:id="d935fn47">Vessel chartered by Japanese Government for
                        effecting exchange of American and Japanese nationals.</note> Shanghai
                    informed Swiss representative restrictions on use internees relief money
                    withdrawn, now able freely spend entire amount allotted. All emphasize necessity
                    increasing allotment 700 to 1,000 dollars as large part required indispensable
                    items not furnished by Japanese such as shoe repairs, clothing, medicines,
                    doctors [and] dentists fees, dietetic food [for] children, invalids. Report
                    canteens somewhat better provisioned. Swiss representative taking steps obtain
                    authorization increase relief allotments and will report results.<note n="48"
                        xml:id="d935fn48">In telegram No. 7088, November 11, the Minister in
                        Switzerland reported that monthly relief allowances had been increased on
                        September 1 to $1200, the equivalent of 54 Swiss francs (740.00115A Pacific
                        War/789).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
